name: Oddish
flavorText: It often plants its root feet in the ground during the day and sows seeds as it walks about at night.
Attack1Text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Gloom
flavorText: The honey it drools from its mouth smells so atrocious, it can curl noses more than a mile away.
Attack1Text: Both this Pokémon and the Defending Pokémon are now Confused.
Attack2Text: The Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

name: Vileplume
flavorText: Its petals are the largest in the world. As it walks, it scatters extremely allergenic pollen.
Ability1Text: Apply Weakness for each Pokémon (both yours and your opponent's) as ×4 instead.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep and Poisoned.

name: Bellossom
flavorText: When the heavy rainfall season ends, it is drawn out by warm sunlight to dance in the open.
Attack1Text: Does 20 more damage for each Colorless in the Defending Pokémon's Retreat Cost.
Attack2Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 50 damage times the number of heads. This Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Tangela
flavorText: Many writhing vines cover it, so its true identity remains unknown. The blue vines grow its whole life long.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Tangrowth
flavorText: Even if one of its arms is eaten, it's fine. The Pokémon regenerates quickly and will go right back to normal.
Attack1Text: Does 30 damage times the amount of Grass Energy attached to this Pokémon. This Pokémon can't use Hundred Furious Lashes during your next turn.
Attack2Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Scyther
flavorText: The sharp scythes on its forearms become increasingly sharp by cutting through hard objects.

name: Heracross
flavorText: No matter how heavy its opponents, it flings them far away with its prized horn.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. If both of them are tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Celebi-EX
Ability1Text: Each of your evolved Pokémon can use any attack from its previous Evolutions. (You still need the necessary Energy to use each attack.)
Attack1Text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Shaymin
flavorText: The flowers all over its body burst into bloom if it is lovingly hugged and senses gratitude.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for 2 Basic Pokémon and put them onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Snivy
flavorText: It is very intelligent and calm. Being exposed to lots of sunlight makes its movements swifter.

name: Servine
flavorText: It moves along the ground as if sliding. Its swift movements befuddle its foes, and it then attacks with a vine whip.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 40 damage times the number of heads.

name: Serperior
flavorText: It can stop its opponents' movements with just a glare. It takes in solar energy and boosts it internally.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 50 damage times the number of heads.
Attack2Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Cottonee
flavorText: Perhaps because they feel more at ease in a group, they stick to others they find. They end up looking like a cloud.

name: Whimsicott
flavorText: They appear along with whirlwinds. They pull pranks, such as moving furniture and leaving balls of cotton in homes.
Attack1Text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon. During your next turn, the attacks of that Pokémon do 40 more damage to the Active Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Petilil
flavorText: The leaves on its head grow right back even if they fall out. These bitter leaves refresh those who eat them.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

name: Lilligant
flavorText: The fragrance of the garland on its head has a relaxing effect, but taking care of it is very difficult.
Attack1Text: Draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage and heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Charmander
flavorText: The fire on the tip of its tail is a measure of its life. If healthy, its tail burns intensely.
Attack1Text: Attach 2 Fire Energy cards from your discard pile to this Pokémon.

name: Charmeleon
flavorText: In the rocky mountains where Charmeleon live, their fiery tails shine at night like stars.
Attack2Text: Does 10 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.

name: Charizard
flavorText: It is said that Charizard's fire burns hotter if it has experienced harsh battles.
Attack1Text: This attack does 40 damage to 2 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)
Attack2Text: Discard a Fire Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Numel
flavorText: The magma in its body reaches 2,200 degrees F. Its hump gets smaller when it uses Fire-type moves.
Attack1Text: Discard an Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Camerupt
flavorText: The volcanoes on its back have a major eruption every 10 years–or whenever it becomes really angry.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokémon is now Burned. Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is also Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Victini
flavorText: It creates an unlimited supply of energy inside its body, which it shares with those who touch it.
Attack1Text: Draw a card.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads.

name: Tepig
flavorText: It blows fire through its nose. When it catches a cold, the fire becomes pitch-black smoke instead.

name: Pignite
flavorText: Whatever it eats becomes fuel for the flame in its stomach. When it is angered, the intensity of the flame increases.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Emboar
flavorText: It has mastered fast and powerful fighting moves. It grows a beard of fire.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Darumaka
flavorText: When it sleeps, it pulls its limbs into its body and its internal fire goes down to 1,100 F.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this Pokémon does 10 damage to itself.

name: Darmanitan
flavorText: When one is injured in a fierce battle, it hardens into a stone-like form. Then it meditates and sharpens its mind.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.
Attack2Text: If this Pokémon has any damage counters on it, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Squirtle
flavorText: It shelters itself in its shell then strikes back with spouts of water at every opportunity.
Ability1Text: As along as this Pokémon is on your Bench, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks (both yours and your opponent's).
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Wartortle
flavorText: It is said to live 10,000 years. Its furry tail is popular as a symbol of longevity.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks during your opponent's next turn.

name: Blastoise
flavorText: The jets of water it spouts from the rocket cannons on its shell can punch through thick steel.
Ability1Text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may attach a Water Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Pokémon.
Attack1Text: Does 10 more damage for each Water Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Psyduck
flavorText: Overwhelmed by enigmatic abilities, it suffers a constant headache. It sometimes uses mysterious powers.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Psyduck
flavorText: When headaches stimulate its brain cells, which are usually inactive, it can use a mysterious power.
Attack1Text: Discard a Fire Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

name: Golduck
flavorText: It is seen swimming dynamically and elegantly using its well-developed limbs and flippers.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Golduck
flavorText: When its forehead shines mysteriously, Golduck can use the full extent of its power.
Attack1Text: Choose 1 of the Defending Pokémon's attacks. The Pokémon can't use that attack during your opponent's next turn.
Attack2Text: Discard all Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Marill
flavorText: The oil-filled tail functions as a buoy, so it's fine even in rivers with strong currents.

name: Azumarill
flavorText: Its long ears are superb sensors. It can distinguish the movements of things in water and tell what they are.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. For each heads, heal 40 damage from this Pokémon.
Attack2Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.

name: Delibird
flavorText: It carries food all day long. When someone is lost in the mountains, it shares that food.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, search your deck for a card and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.
Attack2Text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

name: Oshawott
flavorText: It fights using the scalchop on its stomach. In response to an attack, it retaliates immediately by slashing.

name: Dewott
flavorText: Strict training is how it learns its flowing double-scalchop technique.

name: Samurott
flavorText: One swing of the sword incorporated in its armor can fell an opponent. A simple glare from one of them quiets everybody.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

name: Ducklett
flavorText: They are better at swimming than flying, and they happily eat their favorite food, peat moss, as they dive underwater.

name: Swanna
flavorText: Despite their elegant appearance, they can flap their wings strongly and fly for thousands of miles.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.
Attack2Text: You may discard any Stadium card in play. If you do, this attack does 40 more damage.

name: Frillish
flavorText: If its veil-like arms stun and wrap a foe, that foe will be dragged miles below the surface, never to return.

name: Jellicent
flavorText: Its body is mostly seawater. It's said there's a castle of ships Jellicent have sunk on the seafloor.
Ability1Text: The Retreat Cost of each of your opponent's Pokémon in play is Colorless more.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Cryogonal
flavorText: They are born in snow clouds. They use chains made of ice crystals to capture prey.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Keldeo
flavorText: It crosses the world, running over the surfaces of oceans and rivers. It appears at scenic waterfronts.
Attack2Text: Does 10 more damage for each Water Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Keldeo
flavorText: By blasting water from its hooves, it can glide across water. It excels at using leg moves while battling.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Keldeo-EX
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if this Pokémon is on your Bench, you may switch this Pokémon with your Active Pokémon.
Attack1Text: Does 20 more damage for each Water Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Pikachu
flavorText: It occasionally uses an electric shock to recharge a fellow Pikachu that is in a weakened state.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 40 damage times the number of heads.

name: Voltorb
flavorText: It looks just like a Poké Ball. It is dangerous because it may electrocute or explode on contact.

name: Electrode
flavorText: It is known to drift on winds if it is bloated to bursting with stored electricity.

name: Electabuzz
flavorText: Research is progressing on storing lightning in Electabuzz so this energy can be used at any time.

name: Electivire
flavorText: The instant it presses the tips of its tails onto an opponent, it sends over 20,000 volts of electricity into the foe.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)
Attack2Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.

name: Chinchou
flavorText: It discharges positive and negative electricity from its antenna tips to shock its foes.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Blitzle
flavorText: Its mane shines when it discharges electricity. They use the frequency and rhythm of these flashes to communicate.

name: Zebstrika
flavorText: When this ill-tempered Pokémon runs wild, it shoots lightning from its mane in all directions.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Fire Energy card and attach it to this Pokémon. Shuffle your deck afterward.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this Pokémon does 30 damage to itself.

name: Wobbuffet
flavorText: It desperately tries to keep its black tail hidden. It is said to be proof the tail hides a secret.

name: Spoink
flavorText: Using its tail like a spring, it keeps its heart beating by bouncing constantly. If it stops, it dies.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

name: Grumpig
flavorText: It uses black pearls to amplify its psychic power. It does a strange dance to control foes' minds.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokémon is now Confused.
Attack2Text: If you have the same number of cards in your hand as your opponent, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Duskull
flavorText: It loves the crying of children. It startles bad kids by passing through walls and making them cry.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Dusclops
flavorText: It seeks drifting will-o'-the-wisps and sucks them into its empty body. What happens inside is a mystery.
Attack1Text: Choose a random card from your opponent's hand. Your opponent reveals that card and shuffles it into his or her deck.

name: Dusknoir
flavorText: It is said to take lost spirits into its pliant body and guide them home.
Ability1Text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may move 1 damage counter from 1 of your opponent's Pokémon to another of your opponent's Pokémon.
Attack1Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.

name: Croagunk
flavorText: It rarely fights fairly, but that is strictly to ensure survival. It is popular as a mascot.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Croagunk
flavorText: Inflating its poison sacs, it fills the area with an odd sound and hits flinching opponents with a poison jab.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

name: Toxicroak
flavorText: The croaking that Toxicroak produces before a battle is for churning the poison it has stored in its poison sac.
Attack1Text: If any of your Pokémon were Knocked Out by damage from an opponent's attack during his or her last turn, this attack does 70 more damage.
Attack2Text: The Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

name: Cresselia-EX
Ability1Text: At any time between turns, heal 10 damage from this Pokémon.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon has no Weakness.

name: Munna
flavorText: This Pokémon appears before people and Pokémon who are having nightmares and eats those dreams.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep. If tails, your Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

name: Musharna
flavorText: The dream mist coming from its forehead changes into many different colors depending on the dream that was eaten.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance.
Attack2Text: This attack can be used even if this Pokémon is Asleep. If this Pokémon is Asleep, this attack does 30 more damage.

name: Woobat
flavorText: The heart-shaped mark left on a body after a Woobat has been attached to it is said to bring good fortune.
Attack1Text: Your opponent reveals his or her hand.

name: Swoobat
flavorText: It shakes its tail vigorously when it emits ultrasonic waves strong enough to reduce concrete to rubble.
Attack1Text: For each Psychic Energy attached to this Pokémon, discard the top card of your opponent's deck.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 more damage for each heads.

name: Venipede
flavorText: Using the feelers on its head and tail, it picks up vibrations in the air to determine its prey's location and state.
Ability1Text: If this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon and is damaged by an opponent's attack (even if this Pokémon is Knocked Out), the Attacking Pokémon is now Poisoned.

name: Whirlipede
flavorText: Storing energy for evolution, it sits. But, when predators approach, it moves to stab them with poison spikes.
Ability1Text: If this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon and is damaged by an opponent's attack (even if this Pokémon is Knocked Out), this Attacking Pokémon is now Poisoned.

name: Scolipede
flavorText: It clasps its prey with the claws on its neck until it stops moving. Then it finishes it off with deadly poison.
Ability1Text: If this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon and is damaged by an opponent's attack (even if this Pokémon is Knocked Out), this Attacking Pokémon is now Poisoned.
Attack1Text: If the Defending Pokémon is Poisoned, this attack does 40 more damage.

name: Gothita
flavorText: Their ribbonlike feelers increase their psychic power. They are always staring at something.

name: Gothorita
flavorText: They use hypnosis to control people and Pokémon. Tales of Gothorita leading people astray are told in every corner.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

name: Meloetta
flavorText: The melodies sung by Meloetta have the power to make Pokémon that hear them happy or sad.
Attack1Text: Does 20 more damage for each Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokémon's Echoed Voice attack does 50 more damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Sandshrew
flavorText: It digs deep burrows to live in. When in danger, it rolls up its body to withstand attacks.

name: Sandslash
flavorText: The spikes on its body are made up of its hardened hide. It rolls up and attacks foes with its spikes.
Attack1Text: If the Defending Pokémon tries to attack during your opponent's next turn, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack does nothing.
Attack2Text: Does 10 damage to each of your Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Gligar
flavorText: It clamps on to its chosen prey then jabs the stinger on its tail into the prey while it's stunned with surprise.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Gliscor
flavorText: It dances silently through the sky. When it approaches prey, it can land a critical hit in an instant.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned. The Defending Pokémon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.
Attack2Text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Makuhita
flavorText: It toughens its body by slamming into thick trees. Many snapped trees can be found near its nest.

name: Trapinch
flavorText: It makes an inescapable conical pit and lies in wait at the bottom for prey to come tumbling down.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

name: Dwebble
flavorText: When it finds a stone of a suitable size, it secretes a liquid from its mouth to open up a hole to crawl into.
Attack1Text: Does 10 damage times the number of damage counters on this Pokémon.

name: Crustle
flavorText: When its boulder is broken in battles for territory, it feels unsure and begins to weaken.
Ability1Text: If this Pokémon has full HP and would be Knocked Out by damage from an attack, this Pokémon is not Knocked Out and its remaining HP becomes 10 instead.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Mienfoo
flavorText: In fights, they dominate with onslaughts of flowing, continuous attacks. With their sharp claws, they cut enemies.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 more damage.

name: Mienfoo
flavorText: It takes pride in the speed at which it can use moves. What it loses in power, it makes up for in quantity.

name: Mienshao
flavorText: Using the long fur on its arms like whips, it launches into combo attacks that, once started, no one can stop.
Attack1Text: Discard a random card from your opponent's hand.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 70 damage times the number of heads.

name: Landorus-EX
Attack1Text: Does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)
Attack2Text: You may discard all Fighting Energy attached to this Pokémon. If you do, this attack does 70 more damage.

name: Purrloin
flavorText: Their cute act is a ruse. They trick people and steal their valuables just to see the looks on their faces.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon with the Defending Pokémon.

name: Liepard
flavorText: Their beautiful form comes from the muscles they have developed. They run silently in the night.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokémon is now Confused.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose 1 of your Benched Pokémon's attacks and use it as this attack.

name: Vullaby
flavorText: They tend to guard their posteriors with suitable bones they have found. They pursue weak Pokémon.

name: Mandibuzz
flavorText: It makes a nest out of the bones it finds. It grabs weakened prey in its talons and hauls it to its nest of bones.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 80 damage times the number of heads.

name: Scizor
flavorText: It raises its pincers with eyelike markings for intimidation. It also swings them down dangerously.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks from Pokémon-EX.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon can't use Slashing Strike during your next turn.

name: Skarmory
flavorText: Despite being clad entirely in iron-hard armor, it flies at speed of over 180 mph.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Skarmory
flavorText: Its heavy-looking iron body is actually thin and light, so it can fly at speeds over 180 mph.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.
Attack2Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness, Resistance, or any other effects on the Defending Pokémon.

name: Klink
flavorText: The two minigears that mesh together are predetermined. Each will rebound from other minigears without meshing.
Attack1Text: This Pokémon does 10 damage to itself.

name: Vibrava
flavorText: The ultrasonic waves it generates by rubbing its two wings together cause severe headaches.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.
Attack2Text: Does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Flygon
flavorText: Known as "The Desert Spirit" this Pokémon hides in the sandstorms it causes by beating its wings.
Ability1Text: At any time between turns, if this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon, put 1 damage counter on each of your opponent's Pokémon.
Attack1Text: You may discard a Grass Energy and a Fighting Energy attached to this Pokémon. If you do, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Black Kyurem
flavorText: This legendary ice Pokémon waits for a hero to fill in the missing parts of its body with truth or ideals.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Black Kyurem-EX
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon can't attack during your next turn.

name: White Kyurem
flavorText: This legendary ice Pokémon waits for a hero to fill in the missing parts of its body with truth or ideals.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 40 more damage.

name: White Kyurem-EX
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, attach a basic Energy card from your discard pile to this Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Fire Energy attached to this Pokémon. The Defending Pokémon is now Burned.

name: Rattata
flavorText: It searches for food all day. It gnaws on hard objects to wear down its fangs, which grow constantly during its lifetime.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Raticate
flavorText: With its long fangs, this surprisingly violent Pokémon can gnaw away even thick concrete with ease.
Attack1Text: Discard a Pokémon Tool card attached to the Defending Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Put damage counters on the Defending Pokémon until its remaining HP is 10.

name: Meowth
flavorText: It is nocturnal in nature. If it spots something shiny, its eyes glitter brightly.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Farfetch'd
flavorText: It can't live without the stalk it holds. That's why it defends the stalk from attackers with its life.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Ditto
flavorText: It can reconstitute its entire cellular structure to change into what it sees, but it returns to normal when it relaxes.
Ability1Text: During your turn (before your attack), you may put a Basic Pokémon from your hand on top of this Pokémon. (This does not count as playing that Pokémon or evolving.) This Pokémon is now that Pokémon. (Any cards attached to this Pokémon, damage counters, Special Conditions, turns in play, and any other effects remain on the new Pokémon.)

name: Snorlax
flavorText: When its belly is full, it becomes too lethargic to even lift a finger, so it is safe to bounce on its belly.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 40 damage times the number of heads.

name: Togepi
flavorText: It transforms the kindness and joy of others into happiness, which it stores in its shell.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Dunsparce
flavorText: It creates mazes in dark locations. When spotted, it flees into the ground by digging with its tail.
Attack1Text: Draw 2 cards.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokémon during your opponent's next turn.

name: Taillow
flavorText: It has a gutsy spirit that makes it bravely take on tough foes. It flies in search of warm climates.

name: Skitty
flavorText: It shows its cute side by chasing its own tail until it gets dizzy.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

name: Delcatty
flavorText: The reason it does not have a nest is that it simply searches for a clean, comfortable place then sleeps there.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a basic Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Pokémon. Shuffle your deck afterward.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads.

name: Spinda
flavorText: No two Spinda have the same pattern of spots. Its tottering step fouls the aim of foes.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Buneary
flavorText: By extending its rolled up ears and striking the ground, it can bound so high it surprises itself.

name: Lopunny
flavorText: Extremely cautious, it quickly bounds off when it senses danger.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, heal 60 damage from each of your Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Your opponent switches the Defending Pokémon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon.

name: Patrat
flavorText: Extremely cautious, one of them will always be on the lookout, but it won't notice a foe coming from behind.
Attack1Text: Look at the top 3 cards of your deck and put them back on top of your deck in any order.

name: Watchog
flavorText: Using luminescent matter, it makes its eyes and body glow and stuns attacking opponents.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokémon's Psych Up attack does 30 more damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Lillipup
flavorText: Though it is a very brave Pokémon, it's also smart enough to check its foe's strength and avoid battle.
Attack1Text: Your opponent switches the Defending Pokémon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon.

name: Herdier
flavorText: This very loyal Pokémon helps trainers, and it also takes care of other Pokémon.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon does 10 damage to itself.

name: Stoutland
flavorText: Being wrapped in its long fur is so comfortable that a person would be fine even overnight on a wintry mountain.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon, your opponent can't play any Supporter cards from his or her hand.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this Pokémon does 20 damage to itself.

name: Pidove
flavorText: This very forgetful Pokémon will wait for a new order from its Trainer even though it already has one.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Tranquill
flavorText: No matter where in the world it goes, it knows where its nest is, so it never gets separated from its Trainer.
Attack1Text: Discard an Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Unfezant
flavorText: Males swing the plumage on their heads to threaten others, but females are better at flying.
Attack1Text: Your opponent switches the Defending Pokémon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon.
